div.p:
THe beſt of theſe are found in the Iſleland called Zeilan, ſome ſmall ones are found in Coria, Calecut, Cambaya, Biſnager; there are excellent ones found in the River Pegu, the inhabitants there try them with their mouths and tongues: the colder and harder they are, the better they are; they grow in a certain ſtony matrix of a roſie colour, which if it be tranſparent is called Balaſsium Rubinum;
                        Hoc eſt, Pallatium.
                         for the moſt part it is found in the ſame mine where the Saphire is found: and according to the varietie of its nouriſhment it is found of a mixt colour.
